  Added some (didn’t measure) orange elderflour jam; intended as ripple but left it in too long; kept going to -10; turned to total soup; softness must not be draw temperature but recipe
  drew half at -10 and half at -12; did not get less soupy tho; not sure if it's fpd from the jam inclusion or a serum drain issue from the super high solids w/o stabilizer or related to the pasteurization change; probably serum drain, but will try w/o jam tomorrow to be sure
  Oh well; all into the freezer; will see how it is tomorrow
tasting_notes:
  _very_ soft, but nice to eat right at freezer temp; unsellable but tasty. good flavor.

